  \ west of the meridian of Greenwich, that is to say, on the hundred and fifty\u2011\
  second degree of west longitude.</p>"
- "<p>Cyrus Harding announced this result to his companions, and taking into consideration\
  \ errors of observation, as he had done for the latitude, he believed he could positively\
  \ affirm that the position of Lincoln Island was between the thirty\u2011fifth and\
  \ the thirty\u2011seventh parallel, and between the hundred and fiftieth and the\
