- <p>Herbert was placed on his left side, and was maintained in that position.</p>
- "<p>\u201CHe must not be moved.\u201D said Gideon Spilett. \u201CHe is in the most\
  \ favorable position for the wounds in his back and chest to suppurate easily, and\
  \ absolute rest is necessary.\u201D</p>"
- "<p>\u201CWhat! can\u2019t we carry him to Granite House?\u201D asked Pencroft.</p>"
- "<p>\u201CNo, Pencroft,\u201D replied the reporter.</p>"
- "<p>\u201CI\u2019ll pay the villains off!\u201D cried the sailor, shaking his fist\
  \ in a menacing manner.</p>"
- "<p>\u201CPencroft!\u201D said Cyrus Harding.</p>"
- <p>Gideon Spilett had resumed his examination of the wounded boy. Herbert was still
