  \ Harding was sufficiently acquainted with his history to address him by the name\
  \ of Nemo.</p>"
- <p>The captain concluded the narrative of his life. Cyrus Harding then spoke; he
  recalled all the incidents which had exercised so beneficent an influence upon the
  colony, and in the names of his companions and himself thanked the generous being
  to whom they owed so much.</p>
- <p>But Captain Nemo paid little attention; his mind appeared to be absorbed by one
  idea, and without taking the proffered hand of the engineer,?</p>
- "<p>\u201CNow, sir,\u201D said he, \u201Cnow that you know my history, your judgment!\u201D\
  </p>"
- "<p>In saying this, the captain evidently alluded to an important incident witnessed\
